        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-15T12:18:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The convention I was using in CanvasKit was the build version (1.2.3) followed by a revision number (_v1) so that it\u0027s somewhat clear from the image name what is being used to do the build. Would such a thing add clarity here?  (i.e. take gcc --version and use that as the name)",
      "parentUuid": "77b4be35_a913a5f1",
      "revId": "d561b4563be4936f56d4526fb6b5f22fa75ae3ea",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
